President Obama announced his intent to recess appoint four individuals to fill key administration posts. The individuals are Richard Cordray as Director of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, Sharon Block as a Member of the National Labor Relations Board, Terence F. Flynn as a Member of the National Labor Relations Board, and Richard Griffin as a Member of the National Labor Relations Board. President Obama emphasized the need for qualified public servants to protect consumer rights and uphold the rights of working Americans. Each appointee has a background in law and experience in their respective fields.